lead_paragraph: They said two rockets had successfully hit targets over 850 miles away and were capable of hitting Israel, their enemy.

byline.contributor: Isabel Kershner contributed reporting from Jerusalem, and Rick Gladstone from New York.

headline.print_headline: World Briefing | Middle East; Iran: More Missile Tests Conducted
headline.main: Iran Tests More Missiles in Message to Israel and Biden

snippet: They said two rockets had successfully hit targets over 850 miles away and were capable of hitting Israel, their enemy.
abstract: Iran's Islamic Revolutionary Guards Corps conducts second successive day of missile tests, launching two rockets it says hit targets over 850 miles away and are capable of reaching Israel.
